# Copy to steam-gamescope.env (same directory) to tune the LightDM "Gamebian Steam (gamescope)" session.
# Debian + hybrid laptop: Mesa NVK often cannot run gamescope; prefer AMD RADV for the compositor.
# ICD filename differs by Mesa (check: ls /usr/share/vulkan/icd.d/ — often radeon_icd.json vs radeon_icd.x86_64.json):
#GAMEBIAN_VK_ICD_FILENAMES=/usr/share/vulkan/icd.d/radeon_icd.json
#
# Or pick a device explicitly (see `gamescope --help` → --prefer-vk-device):
#GAMEBIAN_GAMESCOPE_EXTRA_ARGS=--prefer-vk-device <value>
#
# If gamescope hangs on startup with NVIDIA in the mix:
#GAMEBIAN_GAMESCOPE_DISABLE_WSI=1
#
# Kiosk-only: Black screen / tiny BPM in corner — kiosk runs gamescope standalone (no -e) so `-W`/`-H` apply.
# Use your native resolution (`xrandr | grep '*'`) or toggle fullscreen live: Meta/Super+F:
#GAMEBIAN_GAMESCOPE_WH="-W 1920 -H 1200"
# If kiosk fails to start after an update, revert nested mode:
#GAMEBIAN_GAMESCOPE_KIOSK_EMBED=1
